    "Although the application of machine learning in scientific research was not uncommon before, the analysis of the shape of electrochemical signals has never appeared before.",
    "For example, Puthongkham et al.",
    "wrote a mini-review summarizing the latest applications of machine learning and experimental design in MoS 2 46, TiO 2 47 and NaFePO 4 48, theoretical b CVs and c GCDs undergoing different electrochemical processes.",
    "electroanalytical chemistry 25.",
    "Khosravinia et al."
  ]
